Since $AT$ is perpendicular to $TB$, we can treat $AT$ as the height of $\triangle ATB$ and $TB$ as the base. The area of $\triangle ATB$ is $$\frac{1}{2}\times TB\times AT = \frac{1}{2}\times(12-2)\times(12-0)=\frac{1}{2}\times10\times12=60.$$The area of $QABO$ is the sum of the areas of rectangle $QATO$ and $\triangle ATB$, or $24+60=\boxed{84}$.
