label("$x^{\circ}$",(6,0),N);
[/asy]

Since $AB=BC$, we know that $\triangle ABC$ is isosceles with equal angles at $C$ and $A$. Therefore, $\angle BAC = x^\circ$:

[asy]
draw((0,0)--(10,0));
draw((0,3)--(10,3));
draw((2,3)--(8,0));
draw((2,3)--(4,0));
label("$A$",(2,3),N);
label("$B$",(4,0),S);
label("$C$",(8,0),S);
